## Scope

This slice lands the optimization infrastructure that every later fitting/synthesis slice depends on: the library-agnostic optimization interface (┬¦G.1), the single ALGLIB adapter behind it (┬¦G.2), and the flat-`float[]`Ōćä`OpticalSystem` design-variable mapping (┬¦G.3). It is almost wholly net-new orchestration above the existing forward solver ŌĆö the interface is expressed in our own F# records and DUs with no ALGLIB type in its public surface, the adapter is the ONLY file permitted to reference ALGLIB, and the mapping reuses the existing `ArbitraryVariable.getSys` parametrization seam rather than inventing a new mechanism.

No merit assembly, no refinement entry point, no ellipsometry, no inverse fit, no fit-quality, no synthesis, and no UI land here ŌĆö those are slices 010 and 011. This slice's tests prove the two boundary invariants (no ALGLIB type/exception crosses the ┬¦G.1 boundary; the `DesignParameter` fold lands canonical-SI values) in the gated `OpticalConstructor.Tests` host; the full Wolfram end-to-end validation lives in `BerremanTests/OptimizationTests.fs` (slice 011).

## Requirements

### R-1. ┬¦G.1 Library-agnostic optimization interface

This part MUST define the optimization abstraction in our own terms in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Optimization/OptimizationInterface.fs` inside the `OpticalConstructor.Optimization.fsproj` project named in the Part A assembly map. The interface MUST be expressed as F# records and discriminated unions (┬¦0 constraint 1) and MUST NOT reference any ALGLIB type in its public surface, so the physics/fitting code compiles without the library, per ┬¦A.8 ("the physics/fitting code never depends on ALGLIB directly").

The interface MUST consist of exactly:
- `Residual = float[] -> float[]` ŌĆö the vectorized residual function (one entry per target sample), matching ┬¦A.8's `(float[] -> float[])`.
- `Jacobian = (float[] -> float[][]) option` ŌĆö optional analytic Jacobian; when `None` the adapter MUST request numerical differentiation.
- `ParameterBounds` (record: `lower : float[]`, `upper : float[]`) ŌĆö per-parameter box bounds in canonical SI units (┬¦0 constraint 3); an unbounded side MUST be encoded as `infinity`/`-infinity`.
- `InequalityTarget` (DU: `LessOrEqual | GreaterOrEqual` carrying the bound) ŌĆö the one-sided target from 010 ┬¦II.5 ("R Ōēż 0.5%").
- `OptimizationMethod` (DU: `LevenbergMarquardt | QuasiNewtonLbfgs | NelderMead | BoundedLinearConstrained | NonlinearConstrained`) ŌĆö the method selector mapping onto the ALGLIB routines named in ┬¦A.8/010 ┬¦III.4: `LevenbergMarquardt ŌåÆ minlm`, `QuasiNewtonLbfgs ŌåÆ minlbfgs`, `BoundedLinearConstrained ŌåÆ minbleic`, `NonlinearConstrained ŌåÆ minnlc`. `NelderMead` is the 010-required simplex method (010 line 219) whose concrete backend 010 leaves unnamed; its routine binding is deferred per G.2 and MUST NOT be resolved to a spec-invented routine here.
- `OptimizationRequest` (record: residual, optional jacobian, initial `float[]`, bounds, inequality targets, method, `maxIterations : int`, `epsX : float`) ŌĆö the single call payload.
- `OptimizationResult` (record: `solution : float[]`, `finalResiduals : float[]`, `iterations : int`, `terminationReason : TerminationReason`, `success : bool`) where `TerminationReason` is a DU (`Converged | MaxIterationsReached | StepTooSmall | Failed of string`).

The interface MUST expose a single entry point `optimize : OptimizationRequest -> Result<OptimizationResult, string>` (┬¦0 error-handling rule: `Result`, not exceptions). No caching, retry, or progress-callback registry is admitted in this file; progress reporting is wired in G.10 via a separate channel.

### R-2. ┬¦G.2 ALGLIB adapter behind the interface

This part MUST implement the interface from G.1 in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Optimization/AlglibAdapter.fs`, the ONLY file in the solution permitted to `open`/reference ALGLIB. ALGLIB MUST be added as a NuGet `PackageReference` to `OpticalConstructor.Optimization.fsproj` (no new C# project ŌĆö ┬¦0 constraint 1); the GPL free edition is the licensed edition per ┬¦A.8.

The adapter MUST map each `OptimizationMethod` to the ALGLIB routine named in ┬¦A.8: `LevenbergMarquardt ŌåÆ minlm` (`minlmcreatev`/`minlmcreatevj` when a Jacobian is supplied, with `minlmsetbc` for bounds), `QuasiNewtonLbfgs ŌåÆ minlbfgs`, `BoundedLinearConstrained ŌåÆ minbleic`, `NonlinearConstrained ŌåÆ minnlc`. `NelderMead` is the [Standard] NelderŌĆōMead simplex method 010 ┬¦II.5 requires (010 line 219), but 010 ┬¦III.4 names NO ALGLIB routine for a simplex solver ŌĆö its list is exactly `minlm`/`minbleic`/`minnlc`/`minlbfgs`/`mincg`/`lsfit` (010 lines 380-382). This part MUST NOT invent an ALGLIB routine name for the simplex case; the following deferred decision is carried forward VERBATIM as a directive: **the concrete simplex backend for `NelderMead` ŌĆö an ALGLIB routine if one is later confirmed to exist, OR an explicit in-file F# NelderŌĆōMead loop over the G.1 `Residual` closure ŌĆö is deliberately undecided here and MUST remain undecided until that decision is taken, traceable to the 010-required simplex feature; this part MUST NOT resolve it by binding `NelderMead` to a spec-invented ALGLIB routine.** Until that decision is taken the adapter MUST surface `NelderMead` as `Failed "simplex backend unresolved"` rather than silently dispatching to a guessed routine. The adapter MUST translate `ParameterBounds` into the routine's box-constraint call and `InequalityTarget`s into either residual penalty rows (for `minlm`) or nonlinear constraints (for `minnlc`); it MUST convert ALGLIB's completion codes into `TerminationReason` and MUST NOT leak an ALGLIB exception past the `Result` boundary. Linear algebra inside the adapter (normal-equation/QR solves for the LM step) is ALGLIB's own; this part MUST NOT route any matrix operation through `MathNetNumericsMath.fs:5`, and conversely MUST NOT use ALGLIB for any engine linear algebra (┬¦A.8: "ALGLIB is used for optimization only, not for linear algebra"). Extreme Optimization MUST NOT be referenced from this adapter; `ExtremeNumericsMath.fs:5` remains a legacy math-seam reference only, per ┬¦A.8.

### R-3. ┬¦G.3 Parameter Ōćä system mapping (design variables)

This part MUST define the bridge from a flat `float[]` parameter vector to a concrete `OpticalSystem` in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Optimization/DesignParameters.fs`, reusing the existing scalar parametrization seam `ArbitraryVariable.getSys : OpticalSystem -> double -> OpticalSystem` (`Variables.fs:37`) that `calculate` already calls at `Variables.fs:263`. A `DesignParameter` (new record) MUST carry a `name : string`, a `getSys : OpticalSystem -> double -> OpticalSystem` closure (the same signature as `ArbitraryVariable.getSys`), and the per-parameter SI bound pair; an ordered `DesignParameter list` MUST fold left over a base `OpticalSystem` to apply the whole `float[]` vector, in vector order.

The supported design variables MUST be: **layer thickness** ŌĆö the closure MUST rebuild the target `Layer` with `Thickness (v * 1.0<meter>)` (`Media.fs:12`), v already in canonical meters (┬¦0 constraint 3); **dispersion coefficient** ŌĆö the closure MUST substitute into the relevant `OpticalPropertiesWithDisp` (`Dispersion.fs:53`) field; **wedge angle** ŌĆö the closure MUST set the `WedgeLayer.angle` (`Media.fs:34`). Negative-thickness prohibition and physical n-range bounding (010 ┬¦II.5) MUST be expressed as the `ParameterBounds` of G.1 (lower bound 0 for thickness), NOT as a separate validator. This file MUST NOT introduce reflection-based field setting; every mapping is an explicit F# closure the reader can follow (┬¦0 locality rule).

## Non-requirements

- No merit/target-function editor, no local-refinement entry point, no ellipsometric ╬©/╬ö derivation, no inverse fitting ŌĆö those are owned by slice 010 (Part G ┬¦G.4ŌĆōG.7).
- No fit-quality reporting, no needle/tunnelling synthesis or global optimization, no Synthesis/Fit UI page, no Wolfram-reference validation tests ŌĆö those are owned by slice 011 (Part G ┬¦G.8ŌĆōG.11).
- MUST NOT route any matrix operation through `MathNetNumericsMath.fs:5` from the adapter, and MUST NOT use ALGLIB for any engine linear algebra (┬¦A.8); `ExtremeNumericsMath.fs:5` stays a legacy reference only.
- MUST NOT add a progress-callback registry in the ┬¦G.1 interface (G.1 stays callback-free; G.10 / slice 011 wires progress through a separate channel).
- MUST NOT resolve the `NelderMead` simplex backend or bind it to a spec-invented ALGLIB routine (┬¦G.2 deferred decision); the adapter surfaces it as `Failed "simplex backend unresolved"`.
- MUST NOT introduce a new C# project (constraint 1); ALGLIB enters only as a NuGet `PackageReference`.

